                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Poor</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor (only the second
                           component); elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 
 Several groups of lines on the
                           incipit page of Text I, alternating with black lines; groups of lines in
                           the incipit of Text I-2, alternating with black lines; one to three
                           initial lines in the incipit of Texts I-3 to I-8; initial lines or
                           initial word in the incipit of the sections of the daily readings
                           (homilies, absolution prayers, miracles and ʾarke); initial line in the
                           incipit of Text II; first word of each stanza.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#91ra">f. 91ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#91ra">91ra</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘወይዘሮ፡ መድኅን። ወአቡሃ፡ ዘወልደ፡
                              ማርያም፡ ወእማ፡ ወለተ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ወእኅዋ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት። ዘወኀበቶ፡
                              ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ሠጣ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርሀ፡ በመንገሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡
                              በሥልጣነ፡ ጲጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note, written in the main hand, states that the Ms. was
                              donated by Wäyzäro Madḫǝn. The note mentions also the name of the
                              family members and ends with an excommunication against those who
                              stole the book or erased (its text). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tamallas-signs (in the shape of +) indicating the place
                           where the omissions, written in the upper margin, belong: <locus target="#34va">34va</locus>, 37ra.
 - Omitted letters or words
                           inserted interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#4ra">4ra</locus>, 11ra,
                           13va, 52va, 65rb.
 - Pen trial on <locus target="#42r">42r</locus>.
 - Names of individuals crudely written in recent
                           hands: <locus target="#35r">35r</locus>, 38v, 89r.
 - Scribbles:
                              <locus target="#1rv">1rv</locus>, 5v, 17r, 43r, 77r, 91rv.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings of Text I are indicated by the
                              names of the days of the week written in the upper margin, in the main
                              hand: ዘሰሉስ: <locus target="#14ra">fol. 14ra</locus> ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#27va">fol. 27va</locus> ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#37va">fol.
                                 37va</locus> ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#52ra">fol. 52ra</locus> ዘቀዳሚ:
                                 <locus target="#63ra">fol. 63ra</locus> ዘእኁድ: <locus target="#74rb">fol. 74rb</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
